<%block name="title">MIDOSS - Funding and partners</%block>

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
      <h1>Acknowledgements</h1>
      <hr/>
      <h2>Affiliation</h2>
      <p>
        The MIDOSS project is a collaborative scientific research initiative led by researchers
	in the Department of Earth, Ocean and Atmospheric Sciences (<a href="https://www.eoas.ubc.ca/">EOAS</a>)
	and the School of Community and Regional Planning (<a href="https://scarp.ubc.ca/">SCARP</a>)
	at the University of British Columbia (<a href="https://www.ubc.ca/">UBC</a>) and in the
	<a href="https://www.dal.ca/faculty/agriculture/engineering.html">Department of Engineering</a>
	at <a href="https://www.dal.ca/">Dalhousie University</a>.
      </p>
      <h2>Funding sources</h2>
      <p>
        The MIDOSS project is funded by the Canadian Marine Environmental Observation,
	Prediction and Response (<a href="https://meopar.ca/">MEOPAR</a>) network and
	Ocean Networks Canada (<a href="https://www.oceannetworks.ca/">ONC</a>).
      </p>
      <h2>Partners</h2>
        The MIDOSS project has partnered with several government, industry, and non-governmental organizations
	that have provided generous in-kind support, including:
      <ul>
        <li>Environment and Climate Change Canada (ECCC): <a href="https://weather.gc.ca/">https://weather.gc.ca</a></li>
	<li>Fisheries and Oceans Canada (DFO): <a href="https://www.dfo-mpo.gc.ca/">https://www.dfo-mpo.gc.ca</a></li>
	<li>Canadian Hydrographic Service (CHS): <a href="https://www.charts.gc.ca/">https://www.charts.gc.ca</a></li>
	<li>Western Canada Marine Response Corporation (WCMRC): <a href="https://wcmrc.com/">https://wcmrc.com</a></li>
	<li>North Shore Emergency Management (NSEM): <a href="https://nsem.ca/">https://nsem.ca</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>